---
import Card from "../../ui/card";

const benefits = [
  "Exodia OS Comes with BSPWM and 20+ tailor-made fancy Themes.",
  "Cybersecurity tools are preinstalled on Exodia OS.",
  "Currently, 3 Editions exist: Home, Acer-Predator, and Wireless.",
  "Currently, 3 window managers are available: BSPWM, DWM and I3WM",
  "We will add more DEs, WMs and WCs.",
  "Easy installation with Calamares installer.",
  "Exodia is a Rolling Release [Always up to date]",
  "Supporting AUR Repos [with yay]",
];
---

<section class="container mx-auto space-y-24 px-16 max-md:px-8">
  <div class="text-center max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-8">
    <h2 class="header text-gradient">About</h2>
    <p class="text-foreground-light text-start text-pretty">
      Exodia OS is a highly customized Arch-based Linux distribution built for
      and by cybersecurity experts, and also for daily usage, capable of
      performing the strongest pentests and the simplest daily tasks . Even if
      you're not a cybersecurity fanatic, you'll come to love Exodia OS for it's
      aesthetically pleasing interface, tools, and features. Overall, Exodia OS
      is a great distro choice for programming and development, operations
      security, OSINT, and of course daily usage. <br />
      <span class="text-primary">
        Proudly developed in Egypt ðŸ‡ªðŸ‡¬ by Cyb3rTh1eveZ Team.
      </span>
    </p>
    <img src="/desktop.png" alt="desktop" />
  </div>

  <div
    class="grid grid-cols-3 max-lg:grid-cols-2 max-md:grid-cols-1 gap-8 place-items-center *:*:!w-full"
  >
    <Card client:load title="PowerShell">
      Microsoft PowerShell pre-installed pre-configured with Oh My Posh.
    </Card>
    <Card client:load title="TUI Apps">
      Support a whole bunch of TUI Apps RUN: <br />
      <span class="text-sm text-primary">pacman -Sg Exodia-TUI-Apps </span>
      <br />
      to list all available apps
    </Card>
    <Card client:load title="Files Templates">
      Help you to create coding files like web Dev, python, etc... and more
      Files Templates.
    </Card>
    <Card client:load title="EWW">
      Supporting ElKowars wacky widgets(EWW), comes with EWW <br />
      <span class="text-sm text-primary">pre-installed/configured.</span>
    </Card>
    <Card client:load title="zsh">
      Exodia comes zsh pre-installed and pre-configured zsh is the default shell
    </Card>
    <Card client:load title="PredatorSense">
      A kernel module to control RGB & Fan speed in Linux for Acer Predator
      Laptops via: <br />
      <span class="text-sm text-primary"
        >Predator-Sense-CLI <br /> Predator-Sense-GUI</span
      >
    </Card>
    <Card client:load title="CyberSecurity Tools">
      Support tools for all CyberSecurity fields using BlackArch Repos & Exodia
      Repos
    </Card>
    <Card client:load title="BIOS & UEFI"> Supporting both BIOS & UEFI </Card>
    <Card client:load title="Plymouth">
      Supporting Plymouth <br />
      <span class="text-sm text-primary"> exodia-plymouth </span>
      is the default theme
    </Card>
  </div>

  <div class="relative bg-secondary p-12 max-sm:px-6 rounded-lg w-full space-y-8">
    <h2 class="header text-gradient">Benefits</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16">
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-foreground-light space-y-2 pl-8 max-sm:pl-4">
        {benefits.map((benefit) => <li>{benefit}</li>)}
      </ul>
      <img src="/benf-rit-bg.png" alt="desktop" class="" />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
